<br>
It's not finalized but the rotations are taking a huge twist very soon. Each guild being allowed to be in 5 rotations. no more (planes not included). Any small details are being finalized (tiers etc)<br>
<br>
And 1 guild on this server can easily keep everything perma killed. For example, our active roster is close to 100 people. Get all together somewhere, buff up. Send one group to sev (10 mins), one to gore (10 mins), one to here one to there, 2 groups over to trakanon (20 mins cause of fighting in) etc, combine a couple groups for a few other things... oh yeah 1 uber guild alone can finish off every major target from kunark to PoP in just a couple hours, given the motivation and opportunity.<br>
<br>
It doesn't happen cause we respect other people on Karana and adhere to KGC.<br>
<br>
Note to Kellory - GH is infinitely larger then Nightbanned *cough* err nightbane. NB attempted to selectively create a balanced guild by recruiting people from within other ubers that fit their standards. GH is not as selective and does take open apps as of a certain lvl from what I understand. Hell even Valo is bigger then NB heh, and we're more selective then both of em, we only take nice people with good reps.<br>
<br>
**also - something I miss about not playing Lagdalen anymore is those people that send you a tell out of the blue saying hi heh. Like you mentioned, people remember you, even if they only met you once or twice.<br>
<br>
Forrestgump and all the other guilds that went FFA are nothing but schoolyard bullies trying to widen their bank accounts with other people's lunch money. Like every other bullie, they find that when all the kids band together against them, they get pretty small pretty fast.<br>
<br>
Shattering Steel was nothing but a joke. If you want to quote real attempts at FFA, try Eternal Wrath or Nightmare Clan, not the puny lords of gimpdom. They fell apart cause the members were getting shunned and psychologically it was freaking them out. When you loose member base, you loose the guild.<br>
<br>
A serverwide shun is not a small thing to be trifled with. You mentioned in taking the Devil's Advocate position on most arguments, that you enjoy the topic of Psychology. Well, what is the psychological reaction on a person being shunned? How is it effective? Why? And if it doesn't work, then why have we already forced a couple major guilds off the server with it? Shunning is our only way of enforcing KGC. Anything else and we'd all get banned for doing it. It is effective and gets the message across very fast.<br>
<br>
Either way though - the sanctions that KGC has put in place for the moment are basically a general Call to Arms. If your target is up, get to it *NOW* and kill it, dont dick around and get a couple hours of exp in first. If the target happens to pop off of your peak time and you need some help, then ask away for now. Thats all it is, to make less targets available. And everyone knows that running around looking for mobs that aren't up is boring as hell <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.telusplanet.net/public/flarren/Vreesig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> </div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
