<br>
While Grey Hawke and Valoran may have more members, NB is certainly more capable.  At least as far as raiding goes.  Thats not to say the other large guilds cant compete with NB, they just seem to have choosen not to.  I dont like using terms like &quot;uber&quot; and &quot;best&quot; in situations like that.  So I admit I was rather imprecise.<br>
<br>
The main difference that you seem unable to grasp is that the KGC is NOT a small group of people.  The KGC IS the server.  Almost every guild with members above level 45 have reps there.  All have a say.  It is not just a half dozen people making up rules for the server.  It is there to help everyone as equally as possible while preventing the sort of attitude thats common on other servers.<br>
<br>
If Daz and the rest were fed up with a broken system they could have left the server.  They havent.  From the earliest days they simply keep causing trouble for everyone.  Why?  Because in their minds they are more important than anyone else.<br>
<br>
You say you wont fault someone who wanted their epic and took a mob out of rotation because they didnt want to wait?  Well, what about that poor guy who did follow the rules?  Now they're SoL.  Its that sort of attitude that the Karana players, as a whole, have rejected as right.<br>
<br>
If you dont want to leave for whatever reason, thats fine.  But dont then try to explain how great a system that the server has rejected is great because you dont totally agree with them.<br>
<br>
And its not like I dont have my own issues with how the KGC is run.  I do.  As does everyone else here.<br>
<br>
The difference between you and us is that we are willing to work with the system to effect change, whereas you are simply out for yourself.<br>
<br>
It is commendable you remember your friends Yiz.  But in my book the true measure of a person is not in how they treat their equals or superiors, but in how they treat their inferiors.<br>
